    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of thick-skinned, herbivorous, even-toed hoofed mammals having a barrel-shaped, nearly hairless body, short legs, a large head, and a huge mouth with very large incisor and canine teeth; native to Africa, living in or near rivers, lakes, and swamps.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
